## Plan: Add `mistral-instruct-v3` to `common/chat.cpp`

**Only one file changes: `common/chat.cpp`**

### What I found

- All specialized handlers are `static common_chat_params` functions taking `(const common_chat_template &, const autoparser::generation_params &)`
- Message iteration uses `msg.value("role", "")` and `msg.value("content", "")` on `inputs.messages` (a JSON array)
- The dispatcher `common_chat_try_specialized_template()` (lines 1634–1691) detects handlers by searching the Jinja `src` string
- The last existing handler, `common_chat_params_init_gigachat_v3`, ends ~line 1517; `namespace workaround {` begins ~line 1519
- Ministral 3 also uses `[INST]`/`[/INST]` markers — the safe differentiator is the **absence** of `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]`
- `COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY` (chat.h line 148) requires no PEG parser setup

### Change 1 — New handler (insert after line ~1517, before `namespace workaround`)

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template & tmpl,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {

    common_chat_params data;
    std::string prompt;
    std::string system_text;

    for (const auto & msg : inputs.messages) {
        if (msg.value("role", "") == "system") {
            system_text = msg.value("content", "");
            break;
        }
    }

    bool first_user = true;
    for (const auto & msg : inputs.messages) {
        auto role    = msg.value("role", "");
        auto content = msg.value("content", "");
        if (role == "system") {
            continue;
        } else if (role == "user") {
            if (first_user) {
                prompt += "<s>[INST] ";
                if (!system_text.empty()) prompt += system_text + "\n";
                prompt += content + " [/INST]";
                first_user = false;
            } else {
                prompt += "[INST] " + content + " [/INST]";
            }
        } else if (role == "assistant") {
            prompt += " " + content + "</s>";
        }
    }

    data.prompt = prompt;
    data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY;
    return data;
}
```

